snippet.title: Faith Over Fear: Trusting God Beyond Election Day
snippet.description:
In this message, we’re reminded that while Election Day brings uncertainty, our faith in God gives us peace beyond politics. Pastor Daniel shares a story about explaining his vote to his young daughter, emphasizing that our confidence comes not from earthly leaders but from our eternal King. 

What should our mindset be the day after the election? We’re encouraged to focus on three key truths: God is not surprised, the sun will rise again, and Jesus is Lord, no matter who wins. 

By keeping our eyes on God’s promises, we can face any future with faith. 

Join us as we dive into Hebrews 11 and reflect on what it truly means to seek God’s Kingdom first!

snippet.title: Following God and Government: Learning from Romans 13
snippet.description:
In this message, we explore Romans 13 and what it means to follow God while respecting government authority. 

Paul’s words remind us that government is a structure established by God, meant to bring order and peace. But how does this apply to us today? We discuss why respecting authority matters and when our commitment to God should come first. 

Join us as we look at being a good citizen, loving others, and building God’s kingdom, even in challenging times.  [930]

snippet.title: Ezekiel's Vision of Hope: A River of God's Grace
snippet.description:
In this powerful message from Ezekiel 47, we learn about God's promise of restoration and hope. Ezekiel saw a vision of a life-giving river flowing from God's temple, symbolizing the grace and presence of God in our lives. As the river flows, it brings healing, renewal, and transformation, just as God's Spirit does in our hearts today. 

This message reminds us of God's unending love and His desire to awaken us to His vision, both personally and as a church. 

Are you ready to step into the river and allow God's grace to move through you? 

Join us in this journey of faith, renewal, and mission.

snippet.title: Understanding the Ten Commandments: God's Call to Covenant and Love
snippet.description:
In this message, we dive into Exodus 20, the chapter where God shares the Ten Commandments with Moses and the people of Israel. These commandments are much more than rules—they represent God’s deep desire for a relationship with His people. 

We’ll look at how these commandments connect to Jesus' teachings on the greatest commandments: to love God with all your heart and to love your neighbor as yourself. Reflect with us on what it means to live out God’s love, not just in words, but in actions, even when it’s challenging. 

Join us as we explore how to keep God at the center of our lives and truly embody His love.

snippet.title: Mission Sunday: Bringing Living Water to a Thirsty World
snippet.description:
Join us for Mission Sunday as Pastor Ashley guides us through Ezekiel’s vision of life-giving waters and how it connects to our calling. Discover how God’s presence, like a river, can bring hope, healing, and transformation in our lives and communities. 

From serving locally to supporting global ministries, learn how each of us is invited to be part of this flow of grace and love, sharing Jesus' message until the whole world knows. 

Together, we can be a channel of His love and bring living water to those in need.

snippet.title: Trusting God's Provision: Jesus, The Bread of Life
snippet.description:
In this message, we explore what it means to trust in God’s provision, just like the Israelites in the wilderness. For 40 years, God provided manna to His people, reminding them of His faithfulness and care. We reflect on how Jesus, the Bread of Life, fulfills this promise in our lives today. 

Jesus shows us that while physical food is important, what we truly need is the Word of God and His presence. 

Let’s learn how to depend on Him for all of our needs, just as the Israelites learned in the wilderness.

snippet.title: Heart of a Lion: Finding Courage Through Faith
snippet.description:
Join us as we kick off the inspiring new series, Heart of a Lion, a message designed to help us find courage, just like Joshua did when he took on the leadership of the Israelites. 

Every Sunday, we celebrate Jesus' resurrection, a reminder of His love and the courage He gives us.  Today, we’re exploring how God's presence gives us courage to face our challenges and keep moving forward. 

Through Joshua’s story and others, let’s learn how God can help us stay strong, face our fears, and live boldly in faith.

snippet.title: Flowing with Life: Ezekiel's Vision of Hope and Restoration
snippet.description:
In this powerful message, we dive into Ezekiel's vision of the river flowing from the temple, bringing life and healing wherever it goes. Ezekiel, a priest and prophet, witnessed this vision while in exile, and it reminds us that God's presence is with us, flowing through those who believe. 

Just like the river, which starts as a trickle and becomes a deep, life-giving stream, God's Spirit grows in us, spreading hope and transformation. Through this vision, we see how God's power can restore even the deadest places, both in the world and in our lives.

Join us as we reflect on how God's presence can flow through us to bring healing, restoration, and eternal life to those around us. Whether you're facing challenges or seeking hope, this message reminds us that no place is too low or too dead for God's life-giving Spirit to reach.

snippet.title: Stepping into God's Mission: Bringing Life to the World
snippet.description:
Join us for an inspiring message from Rev. Dr. Ashley Goad as we celebrate Mission Sunday! 

Discover how God's river of life, described in Ezekiel 47, flows through us and into the world, bringing hope and transformation. From local communities to global missions, learn how you can be part of this incredible movement of love and renewal. Whether through prayer, serving, or giving, we are called to dive deep into God's mission. 

Let's step into the river of God's presence and bring His Living Water to a thirsty world!

snippet.title: All Saints Sunday: Finding Faith and Courage to Believe in What We Cannot See
snippet.description:
Have you ever faced a tough situation where it felt like there was no way out, but God showed up? This message is about how God leads us through hard times, just like He led the Israelites through the Red Sea. 

We’ll look at the song they sang in Exodus 15, thanking God for His power, faithfulness, and love. What’s the song in your heart? How has God shown up in your life? 

Join us as we explore how we can praise Him for His faithfulness and trust Him for the future.

snippet.title: Why We Shout Hallelujah: Finding Hope in Revelation and Worship
snippet.description:
In today’s message, Pastor Pierce Drake guides us through Revelation 19, uncovering the powerful meaning behind the word "Hallelujah" and why it’s such a vital response to God. This word appears only four times in the New Testament, each time reminding us of God's victory and His holiness. 

We explore the fall of Babylon and celebrate Jesus’ triumph over evil, the promise that God is always on the throne, and how we, as the church, are called to prepare for His return.

As we reflect on All Saints’ Day, Communion, and the upcoming election, Pastor Pierce encourages us to let go of our comfort zones in worship. Whether through song, prayer, or simply lifting up our hearts, we are invited to join the heavenly chorus, proclaiming “Hallelujah” with every part of our lives. This is a message of hope, courage, and unity for believers today.

Join us in worship, and let this message inspire you to lift up your Hallelujah in every area of life!

snippet.title: Bookends of Revelation: Understanding God's Wrath and Grace
snippet.description:
Join us as we dive into Revelation chapters 15 and 16, exploring how God’s final judgments are balanced with His promise of hope and restoration. 

Through the “bookends” of Revelation, we see God's message that He is the beginning and the end, the Alpha and Omega, holding all things together—even during the intense scenes of wrath. We’ll also discuss Jesus’ example of humble service and forgiveness from John 13, reminding us that while we can't control God's judgments, we can choose to live in His grace. 

How can we live as people of grace in a world longing for restoration? 

Let’s unpack these powerful messages together.
